<h2>Patreon</h2>

Finally, reluctantly created an account, because otherwise I just no 
longer had the time to write non-professional reviews. Now I do again. My 
heartfelt thanks to all the strictly swell folks who've signed up. 
Everything will still eventually get posted on Letterboxd (about a month 
after it's written), but if you're the impatient type, <a 
href="https://www.patreon.com/gemko">here's</a> 
where to head. It's only one dollar per month! (A bit more if you want to 
suggest films for me to watch/review, or vote in polls re: same.)

<h2>Other Miscellaneous Writing</h2>
<p>

The assholes at G/O Media made it impossible for me to continue at the 
A.V. Club, where I'd toiled for 13 years. You can still find
my many <a href="https://kinja.com/gemko">contributions</a>,
though, including <a 
href="http://www.avclub.com/features/scenic-routes/">Scenic
Routes,</a> a biweekly column about film scenes of note. The Dissolve is 
no more, alas, but all the  <a 
href="http://thedissolve.com/authors/miked/">work</a> I'm proud to have 
done for the site remains. And <i>Las Vegas Weekly</i> pretty much 
stopped running reviews altogether, but my <a 
href="https://lasvegasweekly.com/staff/mike-dangelo/">stint</a> for them 
ran from <i>Munich</i> to <i>Phantom Thread</i>.

<h2>2023 in Movies</h2>
<p>
We got <a href="caps23.html">reviews</a>. We got a <a 
href="bygrade.html">crazily detailed grid-list</a>. We got a running <a 
href="2023.html">top ten</a> that omits your favorites. <span 
class="added">(Added: <em>Occupied City</em>)</span> 
Come on down! 
</p>


<h2>Viewing Journal</h2>
<p>
Snarkier drive-by comments now get filed on <a 
href="http://letterboxd.com/gemko/films/reviews/">Letterboxd</a>. There's 
also the basic list of <a 
href="mqd24.html#lastfive">every damn film I&rsquo;ve seen this 
year</a>. <span class="added">added: <em>10 Things I Hate About You</em></p>

<h2>Elsewhere Online</h2>
<p>
Increasingly rare random musings and seasonal Skandies updates over at <a 
href="http://enchantedmitten.blogspot.com/">Listen Eggroll</a>. If you're 
curious about what TV I watch, that information is now <a 
href="tv.html">available</a>. And I&rsquo;m on <a 
href="http://twitter.com/gemko">the Twitter</a> like the everybody else.
</p>

<h2>Fun Fact</h2>
<p>
This is among the first 25,000 or so websites ever created, out of more 
than a billion. At this URL since 1996. (Originally on NYU's server in 
'95.)


